race.description: Plenty Valley Retirement Village Mdn Plate
race.comment: Loads of chances and worth watching for moves on any of the debutantes as well. FLASH ALICE (2) showed enough in her first campaign to be on top here. Was overdue throughout winter on the soft tracks but after a good break returns on top of the ground. Drawn for a good run and best figures measure right up. RACEY CASEY (5) is another overdue including a close-up fifth in a tougher race last time. Drawn for a soft run and should be in the finish. WILD ROSES GROW (14) is fitter for two runs back and after placing fresh wasn't disgraced in a tougher maiden latest. Another close to a win.  PRAGUE PRIDE (11) is a first-starter by Prague out of Devita. Well educated, blinkers on and jumps from a favourable gate so worth watching for any market confidence.
